-- Starwood profit rises as occupancy, room rates rise
-- By Rohit T. K. in Bangalore
-- Thu Jul 24, 2014 06:14AM EDT
-- None



July 24 (Reuters) - Starwood Hotels & Resorts Worldwide Inc <HOT.N>, owner of the Sheraton and Westin brands, reported an 11 percent rise in quarterly profit as occupancy and room rates increased.

The company's net income rose to $153 million, or 80 cents per share, for second quarter ended June 30, from $138 million, or 71 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw1v89kla] Worldwide systemwide ReVPAR (revenue per available room) for hotels open at least a year rose 5.3 percent in constant dollar terms.